.SH NAME
cap_inode_need_killpriv \- Determine if inode change affects privileges
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cap_inode_need_killpriv
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
The inode/dentry in being changed with change marked ATTR_KILL_PRIV
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Determine if an inode having a change applied that's marked ATTR_KILL_PRIV
affects the security markings on that inode, and if it is, should
\fBinode_killpriv\fP be invoked or the change rejected.

Returns 1 if security.capability has a value, meaning \fBinode_killpriv\fP
is required, 0 otherwise, meaning \fBinode_killpriv\fP is not required.
